CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 17, 1955, pg. A28, reads: "Prepare For Big Things - Betty Dunson and her creative dancers are shown in rehearsal at Irene Kaufmann Settlement. Recently they were featured with James Moody and the El Dorados at the Diamond Roller Rink on Nov. 25.  They will perform at Horizon Ballroom at the Gateway Center and at the Greater Pittsburgh Airport on Christmas Eve. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight young women, including Betty Dunson in center, wearing dance costumes and leotards, and young man wearing light colored trousers with shredded cuffs, playing bongos, gathered in Irene Kaufmann Settlement
